.TH BLACKHOLE-THREATS 8 "April 2026" "blackhole-threats" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
blackhole-threats \- threat-feed-driven RTBH route server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B blackhole-threats
[\fB-check-config\fR]
[\fB-conf\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB-debug\fR]
[\fB-log-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
[\fB-log-level\fR \fILEVEL\fR]
[\fB-feed\fR \fISOURCE\fR]
[\fB-once\fR]
[\fB-refresh-rate\fR \fIDURATION\fR]
[\fB-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B blackhole-threats
loads a GoBGP configuration and a set of local or remote threat feeds from a
YAML configuration file, extracts IPv4 and IPv6 prefixes, summarises them, and
announces the resulting routes over BGP for remote-triggered blackhole use.
.PP
The daemon maintains the currently advertised route set across refresh cycles.
If a feed refresh fails for a community, the last known-good routes for that
community are kept until the next successful refresh.
.PP
Runtime logs are emitted to standard output in a structured logfmt-style
format suitable for local reading, journald, and syslog-style collection.
Startup logs include build metadata plus the effective runtime configuration
summary.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-check-config
Validate the configuration and exit without starting the BGP server.
.TP
.BI \-conf " PATH"
Read configuration from
.IR PATH .
The default path is
.IR blackhole-threats.yaml .
.TP
.B \-debug
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.BI \-log-format " FORMAT"
Set the log output format. Supported values are
.BR logfmt
and
.BR json .
The default is
.BR logfmt .
.TP
.BI \-log-level " LEVEL"
Set the log level. Supported values are
.BR panic ,
.BR fatal ,
.BR error ,
.BR warn ,
.BR info ,
.BR debug ,
and
.BR trace .
The default is
.BR info .
The
.B \-debug
flag remains as a shorthand for
.BR "\-log-level debug" .
.TP
.BI \-feed " SOURCE"
Add an extra threat feed without editing the YAML configuration. This option
may be supplied more than once.
.TP
.B \-once
Run a single refresh cycle and exit.
.TP
.BI \-refresh-rate " DURATION"
Set the periodic refresh interval. The default is
.BR 2h .
.TP
.B \-version
Print version, commit, and build date information and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/blackhole-threats.yaml
Default Debian package configuration file.
.TP
.I /etc/default/blackhole-threats
Optional systemd environment overrides for the packaged service.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/blackhole-threats/examples/blackhole-threats.yaml
Packaged reference configuration example.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGUSR1
Trigger an immediate feed refresh without waiting for the next scheduled
refresh interval.
.TP
.B SIGINT
Request a graceful shutdown.
.TP
.B SIGTERM
Request a graceful shutdown.
.SH EXAMPLES
Validate a configuration file:
.PP
.RS
.EX
blackhole-threats -conf /etc/blackhole-threats.yaml -check-config
.EE
.RE
.PP
Run a single refresh cycle with a temporary unprivileged BGP port:
.PP
.RS
.EX
blackhole-threats -conf /tmp/blackhole-threats.yaml -once
.EE
.RE
.PP
Port settings are optional. Set gobgp.global.config.port for the local listener
and gobgp.neighbors[].config.port only for remote peer endpoints that do not
listen on standard BGP port 179.
.PP
Trigger an immediate refresh for the packaged systemd service:
.PP
.RS
.EX
systemctl reload blackhole-threats
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemctl (1)
